result.execSummary:
The defendant Dawn M Lozada was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).
  • Theft-Movable Property >$5000-$10,000, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Statutory costs assessed.   If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

No alcohol or controlled substances except by prescription. Random UA's are authorized. Any counseling deemed appropriate by agent; specifically AODA assessment, treatment and after care as well as anger management and cognitive intervention. May not enter into or loiter in front of any taverns, bars or liquor stores. May go into restaurants that serve alcohol but may not drink. Must participate in group based counseling such as AA for the first 18 months of probation.   No contact with the victim business or its employees (person, property, residence or family) without permission of agent.   Defendant must submit a DNA sample as required by law if not previously provided.  Defendant must pay mandatory DNA surcharge on Ct 1 only. Firearm warning given. Voting is prohibited until sentence is complete and civil rights have been restored. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on supervision.

timeConds.notes: Must serve 60 days. Huber is granted for employment. Do not report late or under the influence of alcohol or controlled substances. Absolute sobriety is required. The balance is stayed.

Defendant Dawn M Lozada in court with attorney John Alexander Cabranes.  Erika Frank Motsch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter: Darlene Shue.
The State renews its request to have MS be present in the courtroom as he is a victim as well as a potential witness. Defense objects. The State indicates that they just found out that there is are recording of the interview with the deft. The State has not seen it so she doesn't even know how long it is. Defense indicates that the Statement is of limited value and ask that the Court suppress the tape. Defense indicates that if the State can arrange audio of the tape to be available to the defense this morning, they will review it at lunch. Parties take time to review the DVD prior to the jury being sworn. Jury enters the courtroom at 10:50 am, oath #2 given. The Court gives the jury preliminary instructions. Ms. Motsch gives opening statements for the State. Mr. Cabranes gives opening statements for the defense. The State calls MS - DSAT. Direct by the State. State marks Ex #1-2 large paper boxes, marked box #1 & #2; Ex #2 & 3-back up tapes of data. State moves Ex #2 & 3 into evidence/received. Cross xam by defense. Defense has no objection to the trial going forward despite missing 2 reports. Ms. Motsch indicates that she spoke with Mr. Cabranes last week and she thought they were speaking about the same report when Defense inquired about it. State calls EE - DSAT. Direct by the State. State marks Ex #13-document recording when EE saw deft in the shop, #4-tool log from 2/25/14.  State moves Ex #4 into evidence/received. State marks Ex #7, 8 & 9-photos-Plant Mgr office/engineer's desk; moved into evidence/received. Cross xam by defense. State calls RN - DSAT. Direct by the State. State marks Ex #10, 1 & 12-photos of entries to building and office; moved into evidence/received. State marks Ex #6-photo, State marks Ex #14 & 15-Logs showing attempted connection to HyPro admin server. State moves Ex #14 & 15 into evidence/received. State marks # 16-excel worksheet of what tapes were recovered/still missing dtd 3/10. State moves Ex #16 into evidence/received.

Defendant Dawn M Lozada in court with attorney John Alexander Cabranes.  Erika Frank Motsch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court Reporter: Darlene Shue.
All MIL are addressed. Parties have stipulated that the defendant's statements will come in. State withdraws her request that Danielle Schulman sit at counsel table. The State puts the last plea offer on the record. The defendant rejects the offer and jury trial will commence. The jury enters, Oath #1 given. The State, by Erika Motsch, read information to the jury pool. The State introduces self, those in her office and her witnesses. Mr. Cabranes, for the defense, introduces self, his associates and his witness list. Voir Dire by the Court. Voir Dire by Ms. Motsch for the State. Voir dire by Mr. Cabranes for the defense. The parties exercise their peremptory challenges. The jury is chosen. Parties do not object to the jury as selected. Jurors are admonished and released for the evening. The Court puts the side bar on the record.
